# MongoDB Guidance

- Use MongoDB Atlas as the default production deployment target.
- Local MongoDB is allowed for development and experimentation.
- Centralize connection management and reuse connections safely.
- Keep schema and collection design aligned with core domain entities such as events, sources, locations, personas, and impact assessments.
- Avoid scattering database calls across unrelated UI files.
- Put data access logic behind shared server utilities or repository-style modules.
- Design documents for traceability so facts, sources, and inferred impacts can be audited.
